[woman on phone]
<i>I heard it was an accident.</i>

52
00:04:44,911 --> 00:04:48,998
[woman 2] No, it was no accident, Joan.
Of course the parents are to blame.

53
00:04:49,999 --> 00:04:52,585
Well, I heard they found
the razor in the toilet.

54
00:04:52,669 --> 00:04:56,089
[narrator] <i>Everyone had an opinion
as to why Cecilia had tried to kill herself.</i>

55
00:04:56,172 --> 00:04:58,091
That girl didn't wanna die.

56
00:04:58,174 --> 00:05:00,343
She just wanted out of that house.

57
00:05:00,426 --> 00:05:02,845
She wanted out of that decorating scheme.

58
00:05:04,263 --> 00:05:05,723
[chuckles]

59
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:10,353
[narrator] <i>The most popular theory
held Dominic Palazzolo to blame.</i>

60
00:05:11,312 --> 00:05:13,815
<i>Dominic was the immigrant kid
who was staying with relatives</i>

61
00:05:13,898 --> 00:05:16,776
<i>until his family
got settled in New Mexico.</i>

62
00:05:16,859 --> 00:05:19,404
<i>He was the first boy in our neighborhood
to wear sunglasses,</i>

63
00:05:19,487 --> 00:05:22,532
<i>and within a week of his arrival
he'd fallen in love.</i>

64
00:05:22,615 --> 00:05:24,158
[tennis ball hitting rackets]

65
00:05:24,242 --> 00:05:27,662
<i>The object of his desire wasn't Cecilia,
but Diana Porter.</i>

66
00:05:31,249 --> 00:05:32,917
[sighs]

67
00:05:33,001 --> 00:05:34,502
I love her.

68
00:05:35,294 --> 00:05:37,839
<i>When Diana Porter
left on vacation in Switzerland,</i>

69
00:05:37,922 --> 00:05:39,841
<i>Dominic denounced God.</i>

70
00:05:39,924 --> 00:05:41,092
[boy] I don't know!

71
00:05:41,175 --> 00:05:46,180
<i>And to prove the validity of his love,
he jumped off the roof of his relatives' house.</i>

72
00:05:48,391 --> 00:05:50,143
