01:24:42,245 --> 01:24:46,207
<i>Therese, stuffed with sleeping pills,
was gone by the time we got there.</i>

1176
01:24:48,042 --> 01:24:49,544
<i>Lux was the last to go.</i>

1177
01:24:54,174 --> 01:24:55,175
[coughs]

1178
01:24:55,258 --> 01:24:57,719
[engine idling]

1179
01:24:59,095 --> 01:25:01,514
<i>It's four o'clock on Sunday afternoon.</i>

1180
01:25:01,598 --> 01:25:03,641
<i>Do you know where your children are?</i>

1181
01:25:03,725 --> 01:25:08,646
<i>Bonnie, the youngest Lisbon sister,
strangely wore a 1920s wedding dress.</i>

1182
01:25:08,730 --> 01:25:12,358
<i>Therese Lisbon, a horse lover, had written
to the Brown University admissions office —</i>

1183
01:25:12,442 --> 01:25:15,653
<i>Yeah, Mary always wanted to be a cheerleader,
but her mother wouldn't let her,</i>

1184
01:25:15,737 --> 01:25:18,198
<i>so I was teaching her the cheers.</i>

1185
01:25:18,281 --> 01:25:19,407
[overlapping voices]

1186
01:25:19,491 --> 01:25:21,117
<i>This has been Lydia Perl</i>

1187
01:25:21,201 --> 01:25:23,203
<i>with Channel 8 news.</i>

1188
01:25:32,295 --> 01:25:35,882
[Mrs. Lisbon]
<i>None of my daughters lacked for any love.</i>

1189
01:25:37,467 --> 01:25:40,094
<i>There was plenty of love in our house.</i>

1190
01:25:41,971 --> 01:25:44,057
<i>I never understood why.</i>

1191
01:25:59,447 --> 01:26:01,074
[engine starts]

1192
01:26:16,256 --> 01:26:18,174
[narrator] <i>After the suicide free-for-all,</i>

1193
01:26:18,258 --> 01:26:21,845
<i>Mr. and Mrs. Lisbon gave up
any attempt to lead a normal life.</i>

1194
01:26:24,264 --> 01:26:27,016
<i>They had Mr. Headley pack up the house,</i>

1195
01:26:27,100 --> 01:26:30,228
<i>selling what furniture he could
in a garage sale.</i>

1196
01:26:32,605 --> 01:26:37,110
<i>Mr. Lisbon put the house on the market,
and it was sold to a young couple from Boston.</i>

1197
01:26:39,112 --> 01:26:42,615
<i>We, of course, took the family photos
that were put out with the trash.</i>

1198
01:26:45,660 --> 01:26:47,662
<i>In the end, we had pieces of the puzzle,</i>

1199
01:26:47,745 --> 01:26:50,665
<i>but no matter how we put them together,
gaps remained.</i>

1200
01:26:51,457 --> 01:26:55,086
<i>Oddly shaped emptiness mapped
by what surrounded them.</i>

1201
01:26:55,169 --> 01:26:57,171
<i>Like countries we couldn't name.</i>

1202
01:26:57,255 --> 01:26:59,591
[clock ticking]

1203
01:27:00,967 --> 01:27:03,177
<i>What lingered after them was not life...</i>

1204
01:27:04,512 --> 01:27:07,599
<i>but the most trivial list of mundane facts.</i>

1205
01:27:10,226 --> 01:27:12,228
<i>A clock ticking on the wall.</i>

1206
01:27:13,897 --> 01:27:16,107
<i>A room dim at noon.</i>

1207
01:27:17,525 --> 01:27:21,738
<i>The outrageousness of a human being
thinking only of herself.</i>

1208
01:27:26,784 --> 01:27:30,204
<i>We began the impossible process
of trying to forget them.</i>

1209
01:27:30,288 --> 01:27:32,290
[ticking continues]

1210
01:27:37,253 --> 01:27:39,964
<i>Our parents seemed better able to do this,</i>

1211
01:27:40,048 --> 01:27:42,967
<i>returning to their tennis foursomes
and cocktail cruises</i>

1212
01:27:43,051 --> 01:27:45,345
<i>as though they'd seen this all before.</i>

1213
01:27:47,722 --> 01:27:49,766
<i>It was full-fledged summer again,</i>

1214
01:27:49,849 --> 01:27:53,144
<i>over a year from the time
Cecilia had slit her wrists,</i>

1215
01:27:53,227 --> 01:27:55,229
<i>spreading the poison in the air.</i>

1216
01:27:56,439 --> 01:27:58,858
<i>A spill at the plant increased
the phosphates in the lake</i>

1217
01:27:58,942 --> 01:28:03,279
<i>and produced a scum of algae so thick
that the swamp smell filled the air,</i>

1218
01:28:03,363 --> 01:28:05,573
<i>infiltrating the genteel mansions.</i>

1219
01:28:06,950 --> 01:28:09,911
<i>Debutantes cried over the misfortune
of coming out in a season</i>

1220
01:28:09,994 --> 01:28:12,497
<i>everyone would remember for its bad smell.</i>

1221
01:28:13,998 --> 01:28:16,417
<i>The O'Connors, however,
came up with the ingenious solution</i>

1222
01:28:16,501 --> 01:28:19,587
<i>of making the theme of their
daughter Alice's debutante party</i>

1223
01:28:19,671 --> 01:28:21,297
<i>asphyxiation.</i>

1224
01:28:22,465 --> 01:28:26,302
<i>Like everyone else,
we went to forget about the Lisbon girls.</i>

1225
01:28:27,762 --> 01:28:29,764
[chattering, laughing]

1226
01:29:14,892 --> 01:29:16,519
[chatters]

1227
01:29:17,520 --> 01:29:20,565
[retching]

1228
01:29:21,274 --> 01:29:23,735
Al's got the, uh, acting bug.

1229
01:29:25,278 --> 01:29:27,697
She caught it from Pinkie.

1230
01:29:28,990 --> 01:29:31,993
And I wanna announce tonight
that next fall,

1231
01:29:32,076 --> 01:29:35,455
Alice is going to a little school
in New Haven.

1232
01:29:38,374 --> 01:29:41,461
I hear they have a great drama school.

1233
01:29:41,544 --> 01:29:44,380
In fact, Sam,
I think your father built it, didn't he?

1234
01:29:44,464 --> 01:29:47,550
- [Sam] That's the law school.
- [chuckling]

1235
01:29:47,633 --> 01:29:50,636
We're so proud of Alice.
We really couldn't be prouder.

1236
01:29:50,720 --> 01:29:53,639
- [woman] Aw. Cheers.
- [crowd] Cheers.

1237
01:29:59,687 --> 01:30:01,689
I've had it.

1238
01:30:01,773 --> 01:30:04,025
Good-bye, cruel world.

1239
01:30:10,198 --> 01:30:13,034
No, no, no. You don't understand me.

1240
01:30:13,117 --> 01:30:15,453
I'm a teenager. I got problems.

1241
01:30:16,329 --> 01:30:18,331
[laughter]

1242
01:30:26,798 --> 01:30:29,967
<i>So much has been said
about the girls over the years...</i>

1243
01:30:31,719 --> 01:30:33,930
<i>but we have never found an answer.</i>

1244
01:30:36,974 --> 01:30:39,268
<i>It didn't matter in the end
how old they had been...</i>

1245
01:30:39,352 --> 01:30:41,604
[lighter flicking]

1246
01:30:41,687 --> 01:30:43,523
<i>or that they were girls.</i>

1247
01:30:46,275 --> 01:30:48,444
<i>But only that we had loved them...</i>

1248
01:30:49,529 --> 01:30:51,697
<i>and that they hadn't heard us calling,</i>

1249
01:30:51,781 --> 01:30:54,909
<i>still do not hear us calling them
out of those rooms...</i>

1250
01:30:56,077 --> 01:30:58,704
<i>where they went to be alone for all time...</i>

1251
01:31:00,456 --> 01:31:04,210
<i>and where we will never find the pieces
to put them back together.</i>

1252
01:31:37,326 --> 01:31:40,580
[man] <i>♪ I'm a high school lover ♪</i>

1253
01:31:43,499 --> 01:31:47,795
<i>♪ And you're my favorite flavor ♪</i>

1254
01:31:53,968 --> 01:31:57,221
<i>♪ Love is all ♪</i>

1255
01:31:57,305 --> 01:32:00,683
<i>♪ All my soul ♪</i>

1256
01:32:00,766 --> 01:32:04,270
<i>♪ You're my playground love ♪</i>

1257
01:32:34,258 --> 01:32:38,471
<i>♪ Yet my hands are shaking ♪</i>

1258
01:32:40,473 --> 01:32:45,102
<i>♪ I feel my body remains ♪</i>

1259
01:32:51,192 --> 01:32:54,362
<i>♪ Times don't matter ♪</i>

1260
01:32:54,445 --> 01:32:57,865
<i>♪ I'm on fire ♪</i>

1261
01:32:57,949 --> 01:33:01,786
<i>♪ On the playground, love ♪</i>

1262
01:33:31,357 --> 01:33:34,944
<i>♪ You're the piece of gold ♪</i>

1263
01:33:37,613 --> 01:33:41,450
<i>♪ That flashes on my soul ♪</i>

1264
01:33:48,082 --> 01:33:51,294
<i>♪ Extra time ♪</i>

1265
01:33:51,377 --> 01:33:53,796
<i>♪ On the ground ♪</i>

1266
01:33:54,797 --> 01:33:58,551
<i>♪ You're my playground love ♪</i>

1267
01:34:18,446 --> 01:34:21,532
<i>♪ Anytime ♪</i>

1268
01:34:21,615 --> 01:34:24,952
<i>♪ Anyway ♪</i>

1269
01:34:25,036 --> 01:34:29,040
<i>♪ You're my playground love ♪</i>


